{#
  Example 05 — NHS UK-style language banner.

  Mirrors the NHS UK Design System's pattern of placing a language
  chooser in a top utility banner. The control keeps the
  `locale-chooser` class hook so consumer CSS can target it without
  duplication, plus a `classes` opt for the banner-specific styling.

  Each option is an endonym — the language's own name in its own
  script — which is the NHS pattern. Per-option `lang` on each
  <li role="option"> drives screen reader pronunciation.

  The banner is deliberately narrow, which is what the icon-only
  trigger buys: the button stays one glyph wide no matter how long
  "繁體中文" or "Gàidhlig" is, and the endonyms live in the listbox.

  Caveat worth stating plainly in a public-sector context: this
  control does not work with JavaScript disabled. The button opens
  nothing until locale-chooser.client.js runs. If your service must
  switch language unenhanced, render a plain <form> of links or
  submit buttons instead of (or beside) this helper. See
  ../docs/ssr.md.

  Outcome: a <header> banner with a compact language trigger.
  Opening it lists nine languages, each in its own script.
#}
{% from "../locale-chooser.njk" import localeChooser %}

{% set LOCALES = ["en", "cy", "gd", "ga", "fr", "pl", "ur", "bn", "zh_Hant"] %}
{% set NATIVE = {
    en: "English",
    cy: "Cymraeg",
    gd: "Gàidhlig",
    ga: "Gaeilge",
    fr: "Français",
    pl: "Polski",
    ur: "اردو",
    bn: "বাংলা",
    zh_Hant: "繁體中文"
} %}

<header class="utility-banner" aria-label="Site utilities">
    <span class="brand">NHS</span>

    {{ localeChooser({
        label: "Language",
        locales: LOCALES,
        localeLabels: NATIVE,
        value: "en",
        storageKey: "nhs-locale",
        id: "banner-locale",
        classes: "utility-banner-languages"
    }) }}

    {#
      The closed trigger shows only a glyph, so the active language is
      surfaced here. Visible by default — see ../docs/accessibility.md.
    #}
    <p class="locale-chooser-status" aria-live="polite"></p>
</header>

<main>
    <h1>Welcome</h1>
    <p>Current locale: <code id="current-locale">en</code></p>
</main>

<script type="module">
    import { autoInit, localeName } from "../locale-chooser.client.js";

    const status = document.querySelector(".locale-chooser-status");

    autoInit({
        onChange(code) {
            document.getElementById("current-locale").textContent = code;
            status.textContent = `Active language: ${localeName(code)}`;
        },
    });
</script>
